[
    {
        "text": "At the heart of our Milky Way,",
        "start": 0.9,
        "duration": 2.466
    },
    {
        "text": "hidden by the dust clouds of Sagittarius,",
        "start": 3.36,
        "duration": 3.406
    },
    {
        "text": "lies a trapdoor to eternity:",
        "start": 6.76,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "A supermassive black hole.",
        "start": 9.7,
        "duration": 2.733
    },
    {
        "text": "Or at least astronomers think it’s there.",
        "start": 13.333,
        "duration": 2.467
    },
    {
        "text": "Nobody has ever seen a black hole directly.",
        "start": 15.8,
        "duration": 3.3
    },
    {
        "text": "But astronomers can measure it,",
        "start": 19.1,
        "duration": 2.266
    },
    {
        "text": "by its pull on nearby stars.",
        "start": 21.36,
        "duration": 2.606
    },
    {
        "text": "In 2002, a young blue star",
        "start": 25.166,
        "duration": 3.9
    },
    {
        "text": "named S2 made a sharp turn.",
        "start": 29.06,
        "duration": 2.806
    },
    {
        "text": "The star was moving so fast that",
        "start": 32.6,
        "duration": 2.566
    },
    {
        "text": "only the gravity of four million suns,",
        "start": 35.16,
        "duration": 3.173
    },
    {
        "text": "condensed into a tiny space,",
        "start": 38.33,
        "duration": 2.536
    },
    {
        "text": "could have kept it on course.",
        "start": 40.86,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "That object is Sagittarius A*, the",
        "start": 43.5,
        "duration": 3.9
    },
    {
        "text": "dark hub of our home carousel of stars.",
        "start": 47.4,
        "duration": 3.7
    },
    {
        "text": "If it’s not a black hole,",
        "start": 51.6,
        "duration": 1.633
    },
    {
        "text": "astronomers don’t know",
        "start": 53.23,
        "duration": 1.503
    },
    {
        "text": "what else it could be.",
        "start": 54.73,
        "duration": 1.336
    },
    {
        "text": "Every 16 years, S2 zips close",
        "start": 57.133,
        "duration": 3.5
    },
    {
        "text": "to the black hole, accelerating",
        "start": 60.63,
        "duration": 2.003
    },
    {
        "text": "to speeds of 3,000 miles a second.",
        "start": 62.63,
        "duration": 2.57
    },
    {
        "text": "And this year,",
        "start": 66.133,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
    {
        "text": "astronomers were watching closely.",
        "start": 67.03,
        "duration": 2.203
    },
    {
        "text": "Two teams tracked the star to see",
        "start": 69.866,
        "duration": 2.867
    },
    {
        "text": "what it might betray about gravity",
        "start": 72.73,
        "duration": 2.536
    },
    {
        "text": "and the dark monster it orbits.",
        "start": 75.26,
        "duration": 2.14
    },
    {
        "text": "As S2 passed close to the black hole,",
        "start": 78.033,
        "duration": 2.933
    },
    {
        "text": "time for it appeared to slow down,",
        "start": 80.96,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "reddening the starlight",
        "start": 83.7,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "in what astronomers call",
        "start": 85.5,
        "duration": 1.666
    },
    {
        "text": "a gravitational redshift.",
        "start": 87.16,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "S2 survived its close encounter,",
        "start": 90.233,
        "duration": 2.867
    },
    {
        "text": "but other intruders to the",
        "start": 93.1,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "galactic center have fared far worse.",
        "start": 95.0,
        "duration": 2.266
    },
    {
        "text": "A few years ago,",
        "start": 97.866,
        "duration": 1.394
    },
    {
        "text": "an approaching gas cloud was heated,",
        "start": 99.26,
        "duration": 2.273
    },
    {
        "text": "stretched and torn apart.",
        "start": 101.53,
        "duration": 2.303
    },
    {
        "text": "Now the cloud’s head is rushing away,",
        "start": 104.833,
        "duration": 3.033
    },
    {
        "text": "while its tail is falling into",
        "start": 107.86,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "the black hole’s bottomless gullet.",
        "start": 109.7,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "Last spring,",
        "start": 113.0,
        "duration": 1.466
    },
    {
        "text": "the Very Large Telescope in Chile",
        "start": 114.46,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "captured blurry glimpses of the star",
        "start": 116.4,
        "duration": 2.633
    },
    {
        "text": "and of a cloud of heat",
        "start": 119.03,
        "duration": 1.17
    },
    {
        "text": "that surrounds the black hole.",
        "start": 120.2,
        "duration": 1.766
    },
    {
        "text": "The black hole itself is black.",
        "start": 123.033,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "No light can escape from it.",
        "start": 125.533,
        "duration": 1.997
    },
    {
        "text": "But the area around the hole",
        "start": 128.1,
        "duration": 2.266
    },
    {
        "text": "can be hundreds of times",
        "start": 130.36,
        "duration": 1.473
    },
    {
        "text": "brighter than the sun.",
        "start": 131.83,
        "duration": 1.303
    },
    {
        "text": "Doomed gases swirling inward",
        "start": 133.866,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "are heated to billions of degrees,",
        "start": 136.26,
        "duration": 2.373
    },
    {
        "text": "spraying jets of radio energy",
        "start": 138.63,
        "duration": 2.203
    },
    {
        "text": "into space.",
        "start": 140.83,
        "duration": 0.97
    },
    {
        "text": "Astronomers recently detected",
        "start": 142.466,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "a wobble in the inner ring",
        "start": 144.36,
        "duration": 1.673
    },
    {
        "text": "of the swirling disk: A hot spot",
        "start": 146.03,
        "duration": 2.703
    },
    {
        "text": "that circled the black hole",
        "start": 148.73,
        "duration": 1.57
    },
    {
        "text": "every 45 minutes.",
        "start": 150.3,
        "duration": 1.866
    },
    {
        "text": "That’s the closest we’ve come",
        "start": 152.4,
        "duration": 1.833
    },
    {
        "text": "to probing the edge of a black hole.",
        "start": 154.233,
        "duration": 1.997
    },
    {
        "text": "Anything orbiting closer",
        "start": 156.23,
        "duration": 2.136
    },
    {
        "text": "would fall in and vanish.",
        "start": 158.366,
        "duration": 1.994
    },
    {
        "text": "In the coming months,",
        "start": 160.966,
        "duration": 1.334
    },
    {
        "text": "the Event Horizon Telescope,",
        "start": 162.3,
        "duration": 1.966
    },
    {
        "text": "a planet-size network",
        "start": 164.26,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "of eight telescopes,",
        "start": 165.8,
        "duration": 1.466
    },
    {
        "text": "may produce the first image",
        "start": 167.26,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "of the black hole itself.",
        "start": 169.1,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "At certain radio frequencies,",
        "start": 171.866,
        "duration": 2.367
    },
    {
        "text": "the accretion disk of hot gas",
        "start": 174.23,
        "duration": 1.936
    },
    {
        "text": "becomes transparent.",
        "start": 176.16,
        "duration": 1.24
    },
    {
        "text": "Light curves in the intense gravity,",
        "start": 178.1,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "creating bright arcs",
        "start": 180.9,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "around a dark silhouette:",
        "start": 182.6,
        "duration": 1.866
    },
    {
        "text": "The shadow of the black hole.",
        "start": 185.2,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "A tombstone for matter and spacetime.",
        "start": 188.033,
        "duration": 3.033
    },
    {
        "text": "Black holes don’t only destroy.",
        "start": 192.266,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "As the hole feeds on",
        "start": 194.46,
        "duration": 1.506
    },
    {
        "text": "the material swirling around it,",
        "start": 195.96,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "turbulent magnetic fields can",
        "start": 197.8,
        "duration": 1.966
    },
    {
        "text": "shoot jets of gas above and below.",
        "start": 199.76,
        "duration": 3.106
    },
    {
        "text": "Astronomers studying other galaxies",
        "start": 203.733,
        "duration": 2.433
    },
    {
        "text": "have found hot, bright stars",
        "start": 206.16,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "within the escaping jets.",
        "start": 208.1,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "Newborn stars, born on the run.",
        "start": 210.3,
        "duration": 2.933
    },
    {
        "text": "S2 will swing past the black hole",
        "start": 214.7,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "again in 16 years, to once more",
        "start": 217.5,
        "duration": 3.033
    },
    {
        "text": "walk its tightrope along eternity.",
        "start": 220.53,
        "duration": 2.403
    },
    {
        "text": "By then, we might have glimpsed",
        "start": 223.966,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "the silhouette of doom",
        "start": 225.96,
        "duration": 1.473
    },
    {
        "text": "at the center of our galaxy.",
        "start": 227.43,
        "duration": 1.736
    },
    {
        "text": "Perhaps it will look",
        "start": 229.5,
        "duration": 1.466
    },
    {
        "text": "as mathematically immaculate",
        "start": 230.96,
        "duration": 1.773
    },
    {
        "text": "as Einstein dreamed a century ago:",
        "start": 232.73,
        "duration": 2.57
    },
    {
        "text": "A sphere of no return.",
        "start": 235.3,
        "duration": 2.166
    },
    {
        "text": "But that’s just the outside.",
        "start": 238.166,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "The inside we can only imagine.",
        "start": 240.6,
        "duration": 2.133
    },
    {
        "text": "A mystery as opaque and",
        "start": 243.4,
        "duration": 1.9
    },
    {
        "text": "unknowable as the future,",
        "start": 245.3,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "or time itself.",
        "start": 247.5,
        "duration": 1.433
    }
]